headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Ross Stores (ROST) After A Strong Multi‑Year Share Price Run?
summary: If you are wondering whether Ross Stores is still good value after a strong run, you are not alone. This article will walk through what the current price might mean for potential buyers and holders. At a last close of US$191.83, the stock has returns of 2.6% over 7 days, 4.1% over 30 days, 5.0% year to date, 30.2% over 1 year, 68.8% over 3 years and 76.3% over 5 years. This naturally raises questions about how much of the story is already reflected in the price. Recent coverage of Ross...
